commit.message: Increase version, prepare for release

Increase version, prepare for release

Skipping 1.27 due to prolonged use as prerelease version.

Do not specify `$inc` before `-I$ptkPath`

Avoid build errors due to Tcl/Tk include headers taking precedence,
as reported at https://trac.macports.org/ticket/66157

Not specifying `$inc` later since Tk::MMutil::TkExtMakefile()
appears to already do so.

TODO: Since pTk/Makefile.PL originated from Perl/Tk,
check whether this change is applicable to Perl/Tk and other extensions.

Remove Tk::MMtry usage

Perl/Tk already handles these defines and functions,
although TkTable does not need them.
Tk-TableMatrix did not even have the files being passed
to try_compile().
Update .gitignore, create MANIFEST.SKIP
